NAME
  alocale - show or change the Aurora interface language

SYNOPSIS
  alocale [list | set <code>]

DESCRIPTION
  Manages the locale used for Aurora's localized messages (e.g. afetch labels).
  Catalogs live in /etc/locale/<code>.lua; English is the fallback. The chosen
  language is remembered across reboots and applied at login.

EXAMPLES
  alocale            show the current language
  alocale list       list available languages
  alocale set ru     switch to Russian
